version: 1
display_name: VCFN-9X-000113 - The VMware Cloud Foundation NSX Manager must disable SNMP v2.
global_description: |-
  SNMPv3 supports commercial-grade security, including authentication, authorization, access control, and privacy. Previous versions of the protocol contained well-known security weaknesses that were easily exploited. As such, SNMPv1/2 receivers must be disabled.
osfinger: []  # API/proxy-managed control; not tied to a minion OS grain
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFN-9X-000113
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000516-NDM-000317
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_nsx_manager:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation NSX Manager must disable SNMP v2.
    control_id: VCFN-9X-000113
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      From the NSX Manager web interface, go to the System >> Configuration >> Fabric >> Profiles >> Node Profiles.

      Click "All NSX Nodes" and view the SNMP Polling and Traps configuration.

      If SNMP v2c Polling or Traps are configured, this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      SNMPv3 supports commercial-grade security, including authentication, authorization, access control, and privacy. Previous versions of the protocol contained well-known security weaknesses that were easily exploited. As such, SNMPv1/2 receivers must be disabled.
    remediation: |-
      From the NSX Manager web interface, go to the System >> Configuration >> Fabric >> Profiles >> Node Profiles.

      Click on "All NSX Nodes" and delete any v2c Polling or Trap configurations.
